Rally Export Tool
-----------------

This is a simple tool that reads the XML exports from Rally[1] and spits out a series of story cards ready for print.

[1] http://www.rallydev.com

You'll need:
------------

- Ruby 1.8.6 or higher [2]
- RubyGems 1.1.0 or higher [3]
- Ruby On Rails 2.0 or higher [4]
- Hpricot 0.6 or higher [5]

[2]: http://www.ruby-lang.org
[3]: http://www.rubygems.org
[4]: http://www.rubyonrails.org
[5]: http://code.whytheluckystiff.net/hpricot

Installation
------------

Install Ruby, RubyGems and Ruby On Rails. Instructions can be found at:

    http://www.rubyonrails.org/down

Install Hpricot:

    gem install hpricot

Edit the config/environment.rb file, look for the line:

    ExportConfig::stories_xml_location = "..."

And point at the place where the Stories.xml file from Rally was downloaded.

Start the server:

    cd $PATH_TO/rally-export
    ./script/start # or script\start on Windows

Go to:

    http://localhost:3000/export
    
You should be see a long list of cards. Print it, and you should have 3 3x5 cards per page, ready to be cut and put on your story wall.

- Carlos Villela <cv@lixo.org>
